<br>
Yes, Skathris, I have turned against my master,<br>
Thule, and have chosen to worship Veeshan instead.<br>
She has supreme power over all the gods, and, indeed,<br>
Cazic-Thule is as mortal as a young scaled wolf! He <br>
can be killed, so I've heard, by groups of foolhardy<br>
softskins who want his Slime Blood and his brain!<br>
<br>
I have chosen to follow the Wurmqueen of my own<br>
free will, and for this, I deserve to die, or at least be<br>
sent into exile. I accept this punishment with full<br>
knowledge of my impending doom. If I am driven from<br>
New Sebilis, I will surely face slaughter by softskins, <br>
and this is a sacrifice on my part for the Mother of<br>
Dragons. She will request my life as a token someday.<br>
<br>
As I am a traitor, I only request two things of you:<br>
<br>
1.  A formal exile by any member of your guild, and<br>
2.  An item to wear as a symbol of my outcast status. <br>
<br>
Praise be to Veeshan, and may rotten Thule die again! <br>
<br>
Regards,<br>
Sariyathai, Broodling Shadow Knight of Veeshan<br>
<br>
