of the Brood of Kotiz, humbly penitent, eyes downcast*<br>
<br>
I have made a grave error. You see, in pledging my<br>
loyalty to the odious Veeshan, one of our greatest and<br>
most loathsome foes, I have become a coward and a<br>
traitor to our glorious race. I do not deserve my scales!<br>
<br>
Veeshan, I've discovered, is nothing but a dragon, a ravenous beast of the worst kind, who hates even her<br>
own followers in the Bard occupation. Thule looks upon<br>
us Iksar kindly, and I am a fool to forsake his favor. <br>
<br>
I do my penance before you, Mistress Ithrinn, for all<br>
softskins hate me, except for one Nerissa Clothspinner,<br>
a humble merchant girl, who did not kill me on sight. <br>
Lashun Novashine, a Cleric of loathsome Rodcet Nife, <br>
blasted me into the Void with the red force of his fury!<br>
<br>
If you will reinstate my quivering flesh into the fold, I will<br>
be Thule's slave for all eternity. You, and the members<br>
of our Lizardman race, are the only ones who dare to<br>
approach me with more than pure hatred. At votacht!  <br>
(This is an exile's cry, meaning, &quot;I beg ye--take me!) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kelisk>Kelisk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>No, YOU'RE evil<br>Look out! ...Rar!<br>New lizard Mod!</span><br>  Posts: 1039<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/12/03 11:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=174.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cowardice and Redemption</span><hr size=1> Ha.  You sad, sad little creature.  You fail to remember an important fact:  Not all Iksar share in your weakness.  And a strong brood has no room to allow it.  You defile our Empire, the name of our Emperor, and the name of the Holy Lord Cazic Thule himself!  You forsake these gifts which you are given without more asked in return than loyalty, in the name of a some great Dragon?  Fool!  I hope that wurm taught you to use the great Iksar brain you undeservingly have.<br>
<br>
You ask forgiveness.  Redemption.  You ask to return to our fold.  But for whom?  To serve the Empire, or to serve Cazic Thule as you should have since your hatching?  I think not.  Your guise is transparent, whelp - You seek only an easier path for yourself.  You would accept slavery as an excuse not to loathe yourself for your idiocy... Amusing.<br>
<br>
But to think that you would be accepted to our slave blocks to serve your selfish conscience is laughable.   In the first place, had you paid attention to any of your lessons before leaving, you would know that Iksar are not meant for slavery.  Not even those who forsake the gift of what they are for their own purposes.  For you to think that return to Cabilis will serve you any lighter punishment than live disembowelment under your current circumstances is naive.<br>
<br>
